  "prompt": "Is calibri with font size 9 good for resume?",
  "response": "Calibri at font size 9 is generally considered too small for a resume. While Calibri is a modern and clean font that is widely accepted in professional documents, a font size of 10 to 12 points is typically recommended for resumes to ensure readability. \n\nHere are some tips for formatting your resume:\n\n1. **Font Size:** Aim for a font size of 10 to 12 points for the body text. You can use a slightly larger size (like 12 or 14) for headers.\n\n2. **Font Choice:** Stick to professional fonts such as Calibri, Arial, Times New Roman, or Helvetica.\n\n3. **White Space:** Make sure to leave enough white space to make your resume visually appealing and easy to read.\n\n4. **Length:** Keep your resume to one page if you're early in your career or two pages at most if you have more extensive experience.\n\n5. **Consistency:** Ensure consistent formatting throughout your document, including font sizes, styles, and spacing.\n\nBy following these guidelines, your resume will be more likely to make a positive impression on potential employers.",
